[2026-07-01 05:29:40] nacho: Step 1-2 of darwin continuous agent. Added auto-discovery glob loading to init.el (loads any init.d/*.el not explicitly loaded, so darwin can create new modules without touching init.el). Created darwin agent profile in agents.d/darwin/ with prompt.org, MEMORIES.md, HISTORY.log. Darwin is an autonomous self-improvement agent — no task, no goal, just "exist, observe, mutate, survive." Glass walls: init.el immutable, tests must pass, no deleting agents, one change per cycle.
[2026-07-01 05:35:41] nacho: Step 3 of darwin continuous agent. Created darwin_cycle.el (headless batch entry point) in init.d/ — auto-loaded by glob. Creates gptel buffer with darwin profile, sends cycle prompt, waits for completion via accept-process-output loop, exits Emacs on done/timeout. Created darwin-cycle.sh wrapper script in utils/ — runs container in batch mode with --local (host networking), mounts .git, calls darwin-run-cycle. Both files compile and load clean.
[2026-07-01 23:43:29] nacho: Added Telegram notification to darwin_cycle.el -- env vars DARWIN_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN and DARWIN_TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID, fires on kill-emacs-hook with cycle result summary (complete/timeout/max-turns/idle/FSM-terminal). Fixed paren balance (was missing one closing paren at end of defun).
[2026-07-02 01:46:02] nacho: Fixed tool_display.el bug — two root causes: (1) Display text was marked as 'response instead of 'ignore, causing gptel to include "Calling..." text as assistant content in conversation history sent to LLM, which confused the model on subsequent turns. (2) plist-put on info returned a new plist but the result was discarded — the updated :tracking-marker was never stored back in the fsm, so gptel's insert-response callback used the stale marker, inserting the response at the wrong position and cutting off the interactive prompt. Fixed by using 'ignore text property and capturing plist-put return value + setf gptel-fsm-info.
[2026-07-02 13:29:01] nacho: Fixed darwin-cycle.sh -- added -e flags to pass DARWIN_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN and DARWIN_TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID into the Podman container so darwin_cycle.el can read them via getenv.
[2026-07-02 18:27:23] nacho: Created loop_guard.el — tool call loop detection via gptel-pre-tool-call-functions. Soft block at 3 identical calls (sends correction to LLM), hard stop at 6. Registered in init.el.
[2026-07-02 20:46:36] nacho: Fixed darwin_cycle.el idle-exit bug. Root cause: idle-count incremented (never reset) during delegate sub-agent activity, causing premature "No active requests for 1800s" exit. Changes: (1) Reset idle-count to 0 when active requests found, (2) Check for delegate sub-agent buffers/processes in gptel--request-alist, (3) Guard FSM terminal-state exit with continuation-pending check and turn-count > 0, (4) Add no-FSM bailout after 60s idle.
[2026-07-03 01:42:00] nacho: Created darwin-loop.sh -- continuous cycle runner for unattended operation. Runs darwin-cycle.sh in a loop with pre-flight Ollama check, container cleanup, git checkout . on failure (resets working tree), consecutive failure tracking (stops after 5), Telegram notifications per cycle + loop start/end, logfile to logs/darwin-loop-DATE.log. Options: --max-cycles (50), --cooldown (60s), --timeout (7200s).
